In article <1992May11.040322.21709@microsoft.com> erich@microsoft.com (Eric Hanchrow) writes:

   Ideas, anyone?  References to the literature would be fine.

Read the Knuth, the whole Knuth and nothing but the Knuth 8-)

Specifically, _The Art of Computer Programming, Vol.2 Seminumerical
Algorithms_ ISBN 0-201-03822-6


Over 170 pages cover radom numbers, about 30 address the question:
"What is a Random Sequence?"


